Cleveland Fed Median U.S. CPI: Statistical Summary

-- B y   K r i s t y   S c h e u b l e
-- 
2011-10-19T15:13:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/cleveland-fed-median-u-s-cpi-statistical-summary-table-.html
U.S. inflation rose in September,
according to the Federal Reserve Bank of  Cleveland .  The Cleveland Fed’s median consumer price index rose 0.2
percent in September after rising 0.3 percent the previous month.
Over the past year the index is up 2.1 percent.  The median CPI is a weighted index designed to measure
 core inflation . It is calculated using data released in the
Bureau of Labor Statistics’ monthly CPI report.  Following is a table compiled from the Cleveland Fed:  
